cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the design of an online community for sharing creative work, which has implications for how technology can support social interactions and collaboration among creators. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper presents an observational study of how artists used the Mosaic platform, which involves analyzing user behavior and feedback to inform the design of the platform. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses the social dynamics of the Mosaic community, including the development of social norms around feedback and the benefits of collaborative environments for creative growth. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper mentions natural language processing techniques used to analyze feedback provided by users of the Mosaic platform. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries): The paper discusses the use of an online platform for sharing creative work, which has implications for how digital libraries can support the dissemination and preservation of creative content.
